{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-199","title":"同事相处","sectionId":"chapter-09","sectionTitle":"遇见职场“大红人”","pageStart":990,"pageEnd":994,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":18,"duplicateEntryCount":19,"pages":[{"number":990,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"199 同事相处"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"coworker [ˈkəʊwɜːkə(r)]","headword":"coworker"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.同事"},{"type":"entry","text":"comrade [ˈkɒmreɪd]","headword":"comrade"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.同志"},{"type":"note","text":"◎female comrade女同志"},{"type":"entry","text":"politely [pəˈlaɪtli]","headword":"politely"},{"type":"definition","text":"ad. 有礼貌地，客气地"},{"type":"entry","text":"amiably [ˈeɪmiəbli]","headword":"amiably"}]},{"number":991,"blocks":[{"type":"definition","text":"ad. 亲切地，和蔼可亲地"},{"type":"entry","text":"praise for 因…而赞美","headword":"praise for"},{"type":"entry","text":"learn from the predecessor 向前辈学习","headword":"learn from the predecessor"},{"type":"entry","text":"be supportive of each other 互相支持","headword":"be supportive of each other"},{"type":"entry","text":"take the lead 带头","headword":"take the lead"},{"type":"entry","text":"sense of responsibility 责任感","headword":"sense of responsibility"},{"type":"entry","text":"find fault with 找…的茬","headword":"find fault with"},{"type":"entry","text":"force [fɔːs]","headword":"force"}]},{"number":992,"blocks":[{"type":"definition","text":"v.强迫"},{"type":"note","text":"◎force on施压于…"},{"type":"entry","text":"shirk one's responsibility 逃避责任","headword":"shirk one's responsibility"},{"type":"entry","text":"injustice [ɪnˈdʒʌstɪs]","headword":"injustice"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.不公正"},{"type":"note","text":"◎do sb. an injustice对某人不公"},{"type":"entry","text":"unfriendly [ʌnˈfrendli]","headword":"unfriendly"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.不友善的；不利的"}]},{"number":993,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"fellow [ˈfeləʊ]","headword":"fellow"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.家伙，朋友；同事"},{"type":"definition","text":"a.同事的；同伴的"},{"type":"note","text":"◎fellow worker同事"},{"type":"entry","text":"team [tiːm]","headword":"team"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.队，团队"},{"type":"note","text":"◎team building团队建设"},{"type":"entry","text":"group [ɡruːp]","headword":"group"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.组，团体"},{"type":"note","text":"◎group work小组作业"},{"type":"entry","text":"same rank 同级","headword":"same rank"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"}]},{"number":994,"blocks":[{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 1"},{"type":"example","text":"A：Anyone who doesn't agree with me should just leave. （任何不同"},{"type":"text","text":"意我意见的人都该离开。）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：Don't try to force your opinion on other people. （别把你的意见"},{"type":"text","text":"强加于人。）"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 2"},{"type":"example","text":"A：You seem to be unhappy. What's the matter? （你看起来好像不"},{"type":"text","text":"开心。发生什么事了？）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：The customer sent a letter of formal complaints to our general"},{"type":"text","text":"manager.（客户给我们总经理发了一封正式的投诉信。）"}]}]}